summary: In this blog post, I reflect on the BioIT World 2026 workshop Jackie Valeri and I co-taught on standardizing data science ways of working. I walk through why pain comes before payoff, how to work backwards from what you ship, where to standardize when divergence creates friction, and why people problems beat ROI math. I also cover how standards evolve, how AI lowers the cost of building tooling, and the one thing to start standardizing on your team.
